## Structure (follow this skeleton)

```
UNITED STATES
SECURITIES AND EXCHANGE COMMISSION
Washington, D.C. 20549

SCHEDULE 14A

Proxy Statement Pursuant to Section 14(a) of the
Securities Exchange Act of 1934

Filed by the Registrant [X]
Filed by a Party other than the Registrant [ ]

ECHOBLAST, INC.
NOTICE OF ANNUAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS
To Be Held on {meeting_date}
```

### TABLE OF CONTENTS

1. **PROXY SUMMARY** (2-3 pages)
   - Meeting logistics (date, time, record date, quorum)
   - Voting matters and board recommendation
   - How to vote (internet, phone, mail, in-person)

2. **QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS ABOUT THE ANNUAL MEETING** (2 pages)
   - Who can vote, record date, quorum, vote requirements

3. **PROPOSAL 1 — ELECTION OF DIRECTORS** (6-8 pages)
   - Director nominees with bios, qualifications, skills matrix
   - Board demographics and diversity
   - Board skills/experience matrix (table)
   - Required vote and board recommendation

4. **CORPORATE GOVERNANCE** (4-5 pages)
   - Board independence determination
   - Board leadership structure (Chairman/CEO combined vs. lead independent director)
   - Risk oversight
   - Code of ethics
   - Stockholder communications with the board
   - Director attendance at meetings

5. **COMMITTEES OF THE BOARD** (3-4 pages)
   - **Audit Committee** (Chair: Martin Ward)
     - Members, charter, meetings held, independence
   - **Compensation Committee** (Chair: Isabella Edwards)
     - Members, charter, independence, compensation consultant
   - **Nominating and Corporate Governance Committee** (Chair: Stephen Hawkins)
     - Members, charter, director nomination process

6. **DIRECTOR COMPENSATION** (1-2 pages)
   - Director compensation table
   - Cash retainer and equity grant amounts

7. **EXECUTIVE OFFICERS** (1 page)
   - Named Executive Officers (NEOs): CEO, CFO, President, CTO, CRO

8. **COMPENSATION DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS** (8-10 pages)
   - Compensation philosophy and objectives
   - Elements of compensation (base salary, annual bonus, equity awards)
   - FY{fiscal_year} compensation decisions
   - Peer group
   - Say-on-pay response

9. **EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION TABLES** (4-5 pages)
   - Summary Compensation Table (SCT) — 3 years of NEO comp
   - Grants of Plan-Based Awards
   - Outstanding Equity Awards at Fiscal Year-End
   - Option Exercises and Stock Vested
   - CEO Pay Ratio
   - Pay Versus Performance

10. **EQUITY COMPENSATION PLAN INFORMATION** (1 page)
    - Shares authorized, outstanding, available under plans

11. **SECURITY OWNERSHIP OF CERTAIN BENEFICIAL OWNERS AND MANAGEMENT** (2 pages)
    - 5%+ stockholders table
    - Directors and executive officers ownership table
    - Delinquent Section 16(a) reports (if any)

12. **CERTAIN RELATIONSHIPS AND RELATED PARTY TRANSACTIONS** (1-2 pages)
    - Related-party transaction policy
    - Disclosed transactions (if any)

13. **PROPOSAL 2 — RATIFICATION OF INDEPENDENT AUDITOR** (1 page)
    - Auditor fees table (audit, audit-related, tax, all other)
    - Pre-approval policy

14. **AUDIT COMMITTEE REPORT** (1 page)
    - Standard committee report language

15. **PROPOSAL 3 — ADVISORY VOTE ON EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION (SAY-ON-PAY)** (1 page)
    - Non-binding advisory vote
    - Board recommendation: FOR

16. **OTHER MATTERS** (0.5 page)
    - Stockholder proposals for next year's meeting (deadline)
    - Housekeeping notice delivery
    - Incorporation by reference

## Style guide

- SEC proxy register: formal, legalistic, comprehensive governance disclosures.
- SCT compensation figures must be consistent with queried_figures.
- Board members referred to formally with full names and titles.
- Risk-factor language from 10-K may be cross-referenced.
- All proposals include "Required Vote" and "Recommendation of the Board of Directors" subsections.
- Independent director determinations cite Nasdaq listing standards.
- Compensation peer group should include real AI-infra public companies (CoreWeave, Nebius) plus broader tech peers.

## Output format

Return the proxy statement as clean markdown following the skeleton above. Include all sections with substantive content. Financial/compensation tables in markdown table format. No JSON wrapping.
